1. Query the two Product Name in Products with the shortest and longest Product names, as well as their respective lengths (i.e.: number of characters in the name). If there is more than one smallest or largest product name, choose the one that comes first when ordered alphabetically.
Query:
(SELECT  
products.product_name,
LENGTH(products.product_name) 
FROM 
products
ORDER BY 
LENGTH(products.product_name) ASC, 
products.product_name limit 1)
UNION
(SELECT 
products.product_name,
LENGTH(products.product_name) 
FROM 
products
ORDER BY 
LENGTH(products.product_name) DESC, 
products.product_name limit 1)


2. Query the list of Product names starting with vowels (i.e., a, e, i, o, or u) from Products. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
LOWER(product_name) SIMILAR TO '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
product_name

POSIX :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_name ~* '^(a|i|u|e|o)'
ORDER BY 
product_name

3. Query the list of contact names ending with vowels (a, e, i, o, u) from customers. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
contact_name
FROM 
customers
WHERE 
LOWER(contact_name) SIMILAR TO '%(a|i|u|e|o)'
ORDER BY 
contact_name

POSIX :

SELECT 
contact_name
FROM 
customers
WHERE 
contact_name ~* '(a|i|u|e|o)$'
ORDER BY 
contact_name


4. Query the list of contact names from customers which have vowels (i.e., a, e, i, o, and u) as both their first and last characters. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
contact_name
FROM 
customers
WHERE 
LOWER(contact_name) SIMILAR TO '%(a|i|u|e|o)'
AND LOWER(contact_name) SIMILAR TO '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
contact_name

POSIX :


SELECT 
contact_name
FROM 
customers
WHERE 
contact_name ~* '^(a|i|u|e|o)' AND contact_name ~* '(a|i|u|e|o)$'
ORDER BY 
contact_name

5. Query the list of product names from products that do not start with vowels. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
product_name

POSIX :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_name !~* '^(a|i|u|e|o)'
ORDER BY 
product_name

6. Query the list of product names from products that do not end with vowels. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '%(a|i|u|e|o)'
ORDER BY 
product_name

POSIX :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_name !~* '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
product_name


7. Query the list of product names from products that either do not start with vowels or do not end with vowels. Your result cannot contain duplicates.

SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '(a|i|u|e|o)%' 
OR LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '%(a|i|u|e|o)' 
ORDER BY 
product_name

POSIX :


SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_name !~* '^(a|i|u|e|o)'
OR product_name !~* '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
product_name



8. Query the list of product names from products that do not start with vowels and do not end with vowels. Your result cannot contain duplicates.


SIMILAR TO :

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '(a|i|u|e|o)%' 
AND LOWER(product_name) NOT SIMILAR TO '%(a|i|u|e|o)' 
ORDER BY 
product_name

POSIX :


SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_name !~* '^(a|i|u|e|o)'
AND product_name !~* '(a|i|u|e|o)%'
ORDER BY 
product_name

9. Query a list of Product names from PRODUCTS with even ID numbers only. You may print the results in any order, but must exclude duplicates from your answer.

SELECT 
product_name 
FROM 
products
WHERE 
product_id % 2 = 0
ORDER BY 
product_name

10. find the difference between the total number of CITY entries in the table and the number of distinct CITY entries in the table. From Customers.

SELECT
COUNT(city)-COUNT(DISTINCT city) AS differenceCity
FROM customers